# Agents & LLM

## Roles

- `orchestrator.py` — intent, tool routing, structured response building
- `llm.py` — narrative generation from context + verdict
- `llm_validator.py` — grounding and citation checks
- `response_builder.py` — structured UI payloads

## Rules

- Risk verdict from `RiskEngine` is final — LLM must not contradict ALLOW/CAUTION/BLOCK.
- LLM adds narrative only; UI renders metrics, tables, and factors from structured data.
- Ground replies in RAG chunks, live quotes, and risk preview — never invent prices.
- Trade intent must flow through risk preview before execution-related language.
- Keep `SYSTEM_PROMPT` aligned with `docs/AGENT-CONTRACT.md` and playbooks.

## Do not

- Duplicate structured UI content in markdown replies.
- Skip `validate_llm_reply` / grounding checks when adding new chat paths.
- Move risk evaluation after LLM generation.
